    "created_at": "2015-10-19T22:07:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-19T22:07:16Z",
    "body": "Out of curiosity I started Google Chrome using the command-line and observed that it threw a \"Gdk: shmget failed ... (No space left on device)\" error to STDERR when the errant paste was performed:\n\n```\n[jliverman@centosvbox ~]$ google-chrome-stable paste_test.html\npci id for fd 14: 80ee:beef, driver (null)\nlibGL error: core dri or dri2 extension not found\nlibGL error: failed to load driver: vboxvideo\n[28402:28402:1019/175249:ERROR:sandbox_linux.cc(338)] InitializeSandbox() called with multiple threads in process gpu-process\n[28238:28238:1019/175345:ERROR:browser_main_loop.cc(243)] Gdk: shmget failed: error 28 (No space left on device)\n[jliverman@centosvbox ~]$ \n```\n\nPlease note that all of the other errors are present even with normal (working) operation. Also note that I am using CentOS inside of VirtualBox (version 4.3.28 r100309); I'm not sure if that matters or not. Lastly, Atom doesn't seem to place anything on STDOUT/STDERR when started from the command-line so I got nothing from it for the good or bad (errant) paste operations.\n\nDoes this point to an issue in GTK (as Gdk may be the GIMP Drawing Kit)?\n"
